# Health Check API Tests
# VSCode REST Client format
# 
# Usage:
# 1. Install REST Client extension for VSCode
# 2. Open this file in VSCode
# 3. Click "Send Request" above each request

@baseUrl = {{$shared baseUrl}}

### Health Check - Basic
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Content-Type: application/json

### Health Check with Headers
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Accept: application/json
User-Agent: Cosmic-Gardener-Client/1.0

### API Version Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/health
Content-Type: application/json

### Check Response Time
# @name healthCheck
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Verify Health Response Structure
# @name healthResponse
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

###
# Test response
@healthData = {{healthResponse.response.body}}

### Health Check - Development Environment
# @name devHealth
GET http://localhost:8080/health

### Health Check - Staging Environment  
# @name stagingHealth
GET https://staging.cosmic-gardener.com/health

### Health Check - Production Environment
# @name prodHealth
GET https://api.cosmic-gardener.com/health

### Metrics Endpoint (if available)
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics
Accept: text/plain

### Server Info (Development only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/info
Content-Type: application/json

### Test Error Handling - Non-existent endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/nonexistent
Content-Type: application/json

### Test CORS - Options Request
OPTIONS {{baseUrl}}/health
Origin: http://localhost:3000
Access-Control-Request-Method: GET

